## Context

Toasts are small notifications that appear in the corner of the application.

## Rules

There are two types of toast triggers:

* [server-toast.tsx](mdc:src/lib/server-toast.tsx) for server-side toasts
* `toast` from Sonner for client-side toasts 

### Client Toast

```tsx
"use client"

import { toast } from "sonner";

function MyComponent() {
  return <button onClick={() => toast("Hello")}>Hello</button>;
}
```

### Server Toast

Server toasts are only available in API routes and server actions.

```tsx
import { serverToast } from "@/lib/server-toast";

export const updateProject = orgAction
  .metadata({
    permissions: {
      project: ["update"],
    },
  })
  .inputSchema(updateProjectSchema)
  .action(async ({ parsedInput: input, ctx }) => {
    serverToast("Hello", "error");
  });
```
